summary: It's really upsetting that I still can't like or reblog from people like Jack, Mark, and Dan (Daniel Howell, that Dan. Not Game...
body:
It’s really upsetting that I still can’t like or reblog from people like Jack, Mark, and Dan (Daniel Howell, that Dan. Not Game Grumps Dan). It’s only on mobile, though, but it’s like that feature has been turned off entirely; the only option I have on mobile is to send the post to someone else. Double-tapping the post doesn’t like it, either. It’s really, really annoying and frustrating, and as a mobile user, it makes me not want to use the app anymore because it’s becoming way too inconvenient.

I have to note that this only happens with specific people, too, seemingly the popular youtubers. And they haven’t turned their likes off (is that even an option you can have, preventing people from liking your posts?), because desktop tumblr works just fine.

It’s extremely annoying and disappointing that I can’t reblog from my favorite creators anymore on mobile. I’m no longer flagged explicit, so I had hoped that would resolve the issue, but it didn’t.

@staff you really need to fix this problem. Whatever you did on the day you made that announcement that the guidelines were changing, you need to revoke that feature or fix that bug, because it isn’t helping anyone.
